thread.title: Strongest hurricane ever recorded takes aim at Mexico
thread.title_full: Strongest hurricane ever recorded takes aim at Mexico

author: 13abc
title: Strongest hurricane ever recorded takes aim at Mexico
text:
GUADALAJARA, Mexico Hurricane Patricia barreled closer to Mexico Friday, prompting safety leaders to warn of a "potentially catastrophic landfall" in the southwestern part of the country.
Mexican authorities dispatched officers and issued various warnings.
Although its strength could fluctuate, a Miami-based meteorological center said Patricia is expected to remain an entirely dangerous Category 5 hurricane through landfall.
Experts expected the hurricane's 200-mph sustained winds and torrential rains to slam into Mexico Friday afternoon or night.
Meteorologists have called it the strongest hurricane ever recorded.
According to CNN, the closest contender, at this point, might be Hurricane Camille when it battered the U.S. Gulf Coast in 1969. Patricia looks to be more powerful than that storm, Hurricane Andrew in 1992 and Katrina in 2005.
